job_description:
Nestlé Nutrition, a global company in the Nestlé Group, helps to enhance peoples’ lives through science-based nutrition products and services for consumer groups with specific nutritional needs. Our brands include Nestlé and Gerber maternal and infant nutrition, PowerBar and Musashi performance nutrition and Jenny Craig weight management.
Project Assistant, this is your challenge:

Nestlé Nunspeet is a successful operating unit of the Nestlé Group, the world's leading food, beverage, nutrition and wellness company. Our factory in the Netherlands is producing the most advanced infant formula for both the Nutrition division and the Nestlé Health Science (NHSc) division. Our products with brands as NAN, AL110, Alfaré, Althera and Alfamino are exported to countries all over the world.

In your role you will be responsible for performing administrative tasks such as preparing purchase request, purchase orders, contracts, invoices, and scheduling meetings as needed. You will play a central role of the project engineering team within the challenging environment of our factory in Nunspeet. Provide administration competencies within the project engineering team on all related topics to Procurement, Accounting and Legal according to workflow and procedures.
The ideal candidate has an eye for detail, is confident and can also multi-task without any problems. In addition, it is important that you have good organizational skills and that you can set priorities well.

Are you stress-resistant and do you work in a structured way? Do you enjoy working in a dynamic and ambitious environment? Are you able to work independently? Do you like to take initiative, do you think in terms of solutions, and do you have a hands-on mentality? Then we are looking for you !

Tasks of a Project Assistant:
Coordinate administration of information such as Purchase Request, Purchase Orders, Contracts and Invoices, and scheduling meetings as needed;
Advising, supporting, and stimulate proactive cooperation within the project team, and you take care of procurement requisition in EasyBuy and SAP, from the agenda management, financial, and legal needed by the project for the acquisition of new assets from the bidding process to the payment of vendors including the logistics of goods;
Record all relevant data and event in order to control and monitor contracts (readiness for closing and for managing claims, breach, penalties, etc.);
Support the team in time registration in Kronos and travel assistance in Concur.

What are we offering?
A fulltime position for 40 hours a week (possibility for part time 32-36 hours);
Excellent terms of employment with elements such as a 13th month, factory bonus, corporate fitness initiatives and many other extra’s;
Large variety of training and development programs;
International working environment, entrepreneurship, freedom of thought and action, company pride and an informal culture;

These are the requirements:
At least 3-5 years of relevant experience as an office manager, personal assistant or executive assistant, preferably in an industrial environment;
Demonstrated successful use of analyses, responsible sourcing and supplier relation management;
Excellent social skills and can communicate easily with others;
Organizational skills and service oriented;
Excellent command of the MS Office package and video communication platforms;
A plus if you have experience in database management applications such as SAP, EASYBUY, KRONOS, CONCUR;
Good command (oral and written) of the Dutch and English language.

Any questions?
Our recruiters would be glad to answer any pending questions. Feel free to send your questions to careers@nl.nestle.com and you will receive an answer within 3 working days.
Applying for the job Project Assistant:
Great! If your profile matches the description as described above, we would gladly receive your cv and motivation. You can upload these via the “Apply now” button.
Respect is at the heart of Nestlé's culture and an important part of that is allowing for differences. Differences in people who buy our products and in the workplace. We believe it is important that everyone feels welcome and at home at Nestlé, regardless of their gender, religion, cultural background, age, disability or who they love. We believe that diversity leads to greater creativity and innovation and moves our organization forward. That is why we actively work to create a culture and leadership that offers equal opportunities to all!


Nestlé is 308,000 people strong and are driven by the purpose of enhancing the quality of life and contributing to a healthier future. With more than 91.4 billion CHF in 2018, we have an expansive presence with 413 factories in more than 85 countries. We believe our people are our most important asset, so we'll offer you a dynamic international working environment with constant opportunities for development. Want to learn more? Visit us at www.nestle.com.
